==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*ridanan'', from Indo-European ''*reidh-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[ridan#Old Saxon|rīdan]] (Dutch [[rijden]]), Old High German [[ritan|rītan]] (German [[reiten]]), Old Norse [[ríða]] (Swedish [[rida]]).  The PIE root is also the source of Old Irish [[ríadaim]] (Welsh [[rhwyddhau]]).

